events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Eddie Lacy and T.J. Yeldon gave top-ranked Alabama a pair of 100-yard rushers in the same game for the first time this season, and the duo combined for five scores in a soggy, weather-delayed 42-10 victory over Missouri on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: RBs Lacy, Yeldon power No. 1 Bama

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: LSU freshman Jeremy Hill highlighted a breakout 124-yard, two-touchdown performance with a 50-yard scoring run, and the ninth-ranked Tigers handed No. 3 South Carolina its first loss of the season, 23-21 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 3 Gamecocks can't hold off LSU

events.name: Florida Gators at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Quarterback Jeff Driskel ran for 177 yards and three touchdowns, and fourth-ranked Florida beat Vanderbilt 31-17 Saturday night to remain undefeated going into the Gators' big showdown with No. 3 South Carolina.

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Seth Doege passed for six touchdowns and a season-high 499 yards as Texas Tech shocked No. 5 West Virginia 49-14, ending the Mountaineers' hopes for an unbeaten season.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 5 WVU hammered by Texas Tech

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Quarterback Collin Klein ran for 105 yards and three touchdowns and sixth-ranked Kansas State held off Iowa State 27-21 for its fifth straight win over the Cyclones.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klein, No. 6 Kansas State hold off Iowa St.

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: TJ Jones made a reaching 7-yard touchdown catch in overtime and No. 7 Notre Dame stopped Stanford inches from the goal line to beat the 17th-ranked Cardinal 20-13 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irish stop Stanford on goal line in OT

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Braxton Miller scored on a 67-yard touchdown run, threw TD passes of 60 and 46 yards and produced his third straight 100-yard rushing game, helping No. 8 Ohio State escape with a 52-49 win at Indiana on Saturday night.

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at BYU Cougars

headlines.description: Cody Vaz passed for 332 yards and three touchdowns in his first start since high school and No. 10 Oregon State used a strong start and bigger finish to beat Brigham Young 42-24 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vaz tosses 3 TDs to lead No. 10 Oregon St.

events.name: USC Trojans at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Jawanza Starling forced and recovered Keith Price's fumble inside the USC 5-yard line in the fourth quarter, and the No. 11 Trojans overcame offensive inconsistency for a 24-14 win over Washington on Saturday night.

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: EJ Manuel threw for a career-high 439 yards and four touchdowns and kicker Dustin Hopkins became the ACC's career scoring leader Saturday as 12th-ranked Florida State rebounded from its first loss of the season with a 51-7 victory over Boston College.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manuel, FSU rebound by smoking BC

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Damien Williams broke off a 95-yard touchdown run for the longest rush in Red River Rivalry history, Blake Bell powered his way in for four TDs and No. 13 Oklahoma beat No. 15 Texas 63-21 Saturday for its second straight blowout in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: OU rolls to Red River rout

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Senorise Perry rushed for 101 yards and a career-high four touchdowns to help No. 18 Louisville race by Pittsburgh 45-35 on Saturday.

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Tyler Russell threw for 291 yards and two touchdowns, LaDarius Perkins added 101 rushing yards and a touchdown and No. 19 Mississippi State beat Tennessee 41-31 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miss. St. gets past Tennessee to stay unbeaten

events.name: Syracuse Orange at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Duron Harmon scooped up a blocked field goal attempt and ran 75 yard for a tie-breaking touchdown early in the third quarter and No. 20 Rutgers rode its defense and special teams to a 23-15 victory over Syracuse on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Defense powers No. 20 Rutgers past Cuse

events.name: Fordham Rams at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Deven Drane scooted 76 yards for a touchdown after picking up a fumble and Munchie Legaux threw two TD passes including a 78-yarder to Travis Kelce to lead No. 21 Cincinnati past Fordham 49-17 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 21 Cincinnati routs Fordham to stay perfect

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Louisiana Tech Bulldogs

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel accounted for six touchdowns, including two to fend off a late rally, and No. 22 Texas A&M held on for a 59-57 win over 23rd-ranked Louisiana Tech to hand the Bulldogs their first loss Saturday night.

events.name: Fresno State Bulldogs at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: D.J. Harper rushed for 122 yards and a touchdown and Joe Southwick threw for another score to lead No. 24 Boise State to a 20-10 victory over Fresno State Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harper's legs power Boise St. to 5th straight win

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Denard Robinson threw two touchdown passes and ran for two scores, leading No. 25 Michigan in a 45-0 win over Illinois on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson's 4 total TDs lead Michigan's rout

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Mark Weisman ran for 116 yards and a tying touchdown in the final minute of regulation, and Iowa went on to beat Michigan State 19-16 in double overtime Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa rallies, upends Mich. St. in double OT

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: Venric Mark rushed for 182 yards and two touchdowns to carry Northwestern to a 21-13 victory over Minnesota on Saturday.

events.name: UAB Blazers at Houston Cougars

headlines.description: Houston 39, UAB 17

events.name: Kent State Golden Flashes at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: Kent St. 31, Army 17

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Montee Ball ran for a career-high 247 yards and scored three touchdowns to help Wisconsin beat Purdue 38-14 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball lifts Badgers, sets TD record

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Quarterback Bo Wallace scored four touchdowns rushing, passing and receiving as Mississippi snapped a 16-game Southeastern Conference losing streak with a 41-20 win over Auburn on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ole Miss beats Auburn, ends 16-game SEC skid

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Logan Thomas threw two touchdown passes, J.C. Coleman ran for 183 yards and two long touchdowns, and Virginia Tech (4-3, 2-1 Atlantic Coast Conference) fell behind 20-0, then buried the Blue Devils 41-20 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech erases 20-point deficit, tops Duke

events.name: Temple Owls at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Brandon McManus kicked a 29-yard field goal in overtime and Temple, which trailed for over 59 minutes Saturday, came from behind to beat Connecticut 17-14.
headlines.shortLinkText: Temple downs UConn on McManus' FG in OT

events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Giovani Bernard ran for two touchdowns and North Carolina survived a slew of penalties to beat Miami 18-14 Saturday, handing the Hurricanes their first Atlantic Coast Conference loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bernard, UNC hand Miami first ACC defeat

events.name: Utah Utes at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Brett Hundley passed for 183 yards and a touchdown while rushing for 68 yards and another score, and UCLA's defense largely shut down Utah in a 21-14 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hundley, Franklin carry UCLA to win over Utah

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Stefon Diggs returned the opening kickoff 100 yards, and Perry Hills threw for one touchdown and ran for another as Maryland defeated Virginia 27-20 in Atlantic Coast Conference action on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maryland slips Virginia to stay unbeaten in ACC

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Tyler Wilson was 23 of 31 passing for 372 yards and a career-high five touchdowns to lead Arkansas to a 49-7 win over Kentucky in a game shortened by severe weather.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson throws 5 TDs as Hogs crush Kentucky

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Trevone Boykin threw for 261 yards and four touchdowns, all those scores coming on third-down plays, and TCU won 49-21 at Baylor on Saturday night to end the Bears' nine-game home winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boykin, TCU halt Baylor's home winning streak

events.name: California Golden Bears at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Quarterback Zach Maynard threw for a touchdown and ran for another as California beat Washington State 31-17 on Saturday night.
